+  // assigned events could let us schedule more. We implement a simple look-ahead:
+  // if a greedy pass left events unscheduled, try removing assigned events that
+  // block more events than they replace.
+  //
+  // We use a scoring approach: iterate over all possible subsets is exponential,
+  // so instead we do a heuristic: events that block K other events but are themselves
+  // just 1 event are candidates for removal if K > 1.
+  const totalScheduled = assignedEvents.size;
+  if (unscheduled.size > 0 && totalScheduled > 0) {
